Weather App with Python Django/
├── weather_api/               # Main Django app
│   ├── views.py               # Core logic for weather API call
│   ├── urls.py                # URL routing
│   ├── models.py              # DB models (minimal or unused)
│   ├── key.py                 # Likely contains the weather API key
│   ├── admin.py, apps.py, etc.
│   └── migrations/            # DB migrations
│
├── templates/                 # HTML templates
│   ├── base.html              # Base layout
│   └── weather_api/          
│       ├── home.html          # Homepage (weather input form)
│       └── results.html       # Weather results page
│
├── staticfiles/              # All static files (CSS, JS, images)
│   ├── admin/                # Default Django admin CSS/JS
│   ├── css/, js/, fonts/, images/
│
├── manage.py                 # Django's command-line utility
└── db.sqlite3 (maybe missing until first run)
